Overview

Walton is the youngest child of Wal-Mart Stores founder Sam Walton. She is a co-manager of Walton Enterprises, one of two family holding companies that control about half of the world's biggest retailer. The Bentonville, Arkansas-based company reported revenue of $486 billion in the year to Jan. 31, 2017.

